# GitHub remote (VoxBulk)

This project uses **one** GitHub repository:

- **Repo:** `https://github.com/menasimuk-hub/Vox-new.git`
- **Owner/repo:** `menasimuk-hub/Vox-new`
- **Default branch:** `main`

## Agent rules

- **Push and pull only to `origin`** on `menasimuk-hub/Vox-new`.
- **Do not** push to, pull from, or reference `menasimuk-hub/Vox` (legacy duplicate).
- **Do not** add or use a second remote for the same codebase unless the user explicitly asks.
- After commits, run: `git push origin main`
- VPS deploy: `git pull origin main` then `./deploy-vps.sh`

## Clone (new machine)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/menasimuk-hub/Vox-new.git
cd Vox-new
```

## If `origin` points elsewhere

```bash
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/menasimuk-hub/Vox-new.git
git fetch origin
git branch -u origin/main main
```
